        <p style="padding: 10px;"><strong style="color:black;">Attending Centre, I balanced my technical education with art classes and working for the library. I served on the Black Stem Coalation execitive team, volunteered at The Gladys Project, tutored local elementary school students and often found myself babysiting professors' kids. </strong></p>
    </div>
<!--Professional Work -->             
    <h2 style="text-align:left;margin-top: 30px;font-size: 40px;color: #darkgrey;font-style: oblique;">Professional Work</h2>                    
    <div class="container" style="background-color:#e5e5e5;padding:5px;text-align:center;">
        <p style="padding: 20px;"><strong style="color:black;"> During the course of my academic career, I managed to accrue nearly 3 years of work experience. With the privilege of working for Centre College in a digital archivist assistant role, I learned valuable professional skills such as digital data management, programming and software systems. I worked webscarping, creating metadata, creating content and tracking statistics for social media accounts.</strong></p>
    </div>
<!--Published Work -->
    <h2 style="text-align:left;margin-top: 30px;font-size: 40px;color: #darkgrey;font-style: oblique;">Published Work</h2><h3>Software Development</h3>
    <div class="container" style="background-color:#e5e5e5;padding:5px;text-align:center;">
        <p style="padding: 20px;"><strong style="color:black;word-break: break-all;"> During Junior year, I was granted the opportunity to work on a bioinformatics project with a Centre College computer science professor developing a customizable heat map and a program to run protein compounds through AutoCad Vina software.</strong></p> 
